# Day 10 — Dockerized Log Monitoring System (Nginx + Flask)

## Objective
Today I built a Dockerized log monitoring system to practice containerization, reverse proxy configuration, and basic log analysis.

## What I Built
I created a small project where:
- A Flask API runs inside a Docker container.
- Nginx acts as a reverse proxy.
- Docker Compose manages both containers.
- Requests go through Nginx and are forwarded to the Flask application.
- Logs are generated and analyzed using Linux command-line tools.

## Architecture

User Request  
↓  
Nginx Reverse Proxy (Container)  
↓  
Flask API (Container)  
↓  
Access Logs  
↓  
Log Analysis using Linux CLI Tools  

